Another crucial segmentation factor in the pouches market is based on the product type. Stand-up pouches are favored for their convenience in storage and display, while flat pouches are preferred for their cost-effectiveness in packaging solutions. Spout pouches, with their design catering to liquids and semi-liquids, are finding increased application in various industries for their practicality.

The application segment plays a pivotal role in driving the demand for pouches in the market. The food & beverage industry accounts for a significant share of the market, driven by the need for convenient and attractive packaging solutions to appeal to consumers. The pharmaceuticals sector is also witnessing growth in the pouches market, driven by the demand for secure and tamper-proof packaging for medicines and healthcare products. Additionally, the personal care & cosmetics industry is adopting pouch packaging for its versatility and visual appeal in product presentation.

